Module kivakit.core.collections
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.list

Interface ShortList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Countable, NamedObject, PrimitiveList, ShortCollection, ShortIterable, Sized
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ShortArray
    public interface ShortList
extends ShortCollection, PrimitiveList
    A collection of primitive short values. All primitive collections have a name that can be retrieved with NamedObject.objectName() and a size retrieved with Sized.size() and they can be emptied with ShortCollection.clear(). Values in this collection can be iterated with an ShortIterator returned by the ShortIterable.iterator() method.

    New values can be added with ShortCollection.add(short), ShortCollection.addAll(ShortCollection) and ShortCollection.addAll(short[]) and removed with ShortCollection.remove(short). In addition, Quantizable values can be added with ShortCollection.addAll(List), where each value is quantized via Quantizable.quantum() before being added.

    Whether a given value or collection of values is in the collection can be determined with ShortCollection.contains(short) and ShortCollection.containsAll(ShortCollection).

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    Named, Sized, ShortIterable
